subject: JUnit 4.4 Javadoc?
msgSnippet: JUnit 4.4 includes a lot of new stuff, but the only javadoc available online is from version 4.0.  Strangely, there seem to be two different 4.0 javadoc URLs,
messageBody:
JUnit 4.4 includes a lot of new stuff, but the only javadoc available
online is from version 4.0. Strangely, there seem to be two different
4.0 javadoc URLs, one of which includes the examples:

http://junit.sourceforge.net/javadoc/
http://junit.sourceforge.net/javadoc_40/

Could somebody make a "/javadoc_44" and update links to refer to the
new 4.4 Javadoc? Or make the 4.4 Javadoc available on the web some
other way?

-Dan
